name: Whitetip Clover
overview: Native annual plant meaning seed to germinate and die in the same year. Species of clover an annual herb with leaves of three that have serrated edges. Flowers with a single flower that is purple and commonly has a white tip. Nitrogen fixer meaning nitrogen converted to ammonia. Hermaphrodite flower.
habitat: Ranges southern Alaska to Baja California. Prefer spend ground in vernal pools, along stream, and moist meadow. Also found throughout Sierra Nevada and Cascade Mountains.
